cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with sequence learning problems, which are often studied in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new unit for RNNs, which is related to machine learning and deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The MZU is designed to capture long-range dependencies, which is a common problem in RNNs. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on character-level language modeling and sentiment analysis, which are tasks related to computer vision and image processing. Hence, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible category.
